OL,3,CAssisted dying would be 'wrong',
OL,4,CArchbishop of Westminster tells ITV
OL,5,CNews
OL,7,F"I've been at many deathbeds,
OL,8,Fincluding my own brother, including
OL,9,Fclose friends," the Archbishop said,
OL,10,Fadding that palliative care and
OL,11,Fsufficient pain relief are crucial
OL,12,Ftowards the end of life.
OL,14,FBut, he added, "there's a huge
OL,15,Fdifference between allowing nature to
OL,16,Ftake its course, giving solid support
OL,17,Fin pain management, and deliberately
OL,18,Fand directly ending a person's life."
OL,20,F"I think the difference is perfectly
OL,21,Fclear when you're there."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
