OL,3,CAssisted dying would be 'wrong',
OL,4,CArchbishop of Westminster tells ITV
OL,5,CNews
OL,7,FHelen Skelton told ITV News that the
OL,8,Fchoice to have an assisted death would
OL,9,Fgive her freedom for joy.
OL,11,FLast week, Paul Brand spoke to Helen
OL,12,FSkelton, who has terminal stage four
OL,13,Fbreast cancer. Helen is allergic to
OL,14,Fmorphine and other opioids, and fears
OL,15,Fher death will be painful.
OL,17,FShe said assisted dying would offer
OL,18,Fher "so much freedom for joy and less
OL,19,Ffear."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
