OL,3,CAssisted dying would be 'wrong',
OL,4,CArchbishop of Westminster tells ITV
OL,5,CNews
OL,7,FIf passed, the law would arguably be
OL,8,Fthe most significant social change
OL,9,Fsince the legalisation of abortion and
OL,10,Fdecriminalisation of homosexuality in
OL,11,Fthe 1960s.
OL,13,FCardinal Nichols previously attacked
OL,14,FDavid Cameron's government for
OL,15,Flegalising gay marriage, calling the
OL,16,Fplans "shambolic" and "Orwellian".
OL,18,FHe penned a pastoral letter in 2012,
OL,19,Femphasising "the importance of having
OL,20,Fa clear vision of marriage and family,
OL,21,Fbased on human nature itself".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
